----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><div _ngcontent-ng-c883040262="" class="response-content ng-tns-c1390744527-680"><!----><div _ngcontent-ng-c883040262="" class="thoughts-container ng-star-inserted"><div _ngcontent-ng-c883040262="" class="thoughts-content ng-star-inserted"><div _ngcontent-ng-c883040262="" class="thoughts-wrapper"><!----><model-thoughts _ngcontent-ng-c883040262="" data-test-id="model-thoughts" _nghost-ng-c3976548746="" class="ng-tns-c3976548746-682 ng-star-inserted" style="height: auto;"><div _ngcontent-ng-c3976548746="" xapautoid="" class="model-thoughts ng-tns-c3976548746-682 is-mobile"><div _ngcontent-ng-c3976548746="" class="thoughts-header ng-tns-c3976548746-682"><button _ngcontent-ng-c3976548746="" mat-button="" data-test-id="thoughts-header-button" class="mdc-button mat-mdc-button-base thoughts-header-button ng-tns-c3976548746-682 mat-mdc-button mat-unthemed" mat-ripple-loader-uninitialized="" mat-ripple-loader-class-name="mat-mdc-button-ripple" aria-controls="" aria-expanded="false" jslog="247951;track:generic_click,impression"><span class="mat-mdc-button-persistent-ripple mdc-button__ripple"></span><span class="mdc-button__label"><div _ngcontent-ng-c3976548746="" class="thoughts-header-button-content animated-content"><div _ngcontent-ng-c3976548746="" role="status" class="thoughts-header-button-label ng-tns-c3976548746-682"><!----><span _ngcontent-ng-c3976548746="" class="ng-tns-c3976548746-682 ng-star-inserted">Show thinking</span><!----></div><div _ngcontent-ng-c3976548746="" class="thoughts-header-button-icons ng-tns-c3976548746-682"><!----><mat-icon _ngcontent-ng-c3976548746="" role="img" fonticon="expand_more" class="mat-icon notranslate thoughts-header-button-icon ng-tns-c3976548746-682 google-symbols mat-ligature-font mat-icon-no-color ng-star-inserted" aria-hidden="true" data-mat-icon-type="font" data-mat-icon-name="expand_more"></mat-icon><!----></div></div></span><!----><span class="mat-focus-indicator"></span><span class="mat-mdc-button-touch-target"></span></button></div><!----><!----></div></model-thoughts><!----></div><!----></div><!----></div><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><h2 _ngcontent-ng-c883040262="" class="cdk-visually-hidden screen-reader-model-response-label ng-star-inserted"> Sage  said </h2><!----><!----><!----><!----><structured-content-container _ngcontent-ng-c883040262="" class="model-response-text has-thoughts is-mobile processing-state-visible enable-2026q1-formatting-improvements ng-star-inserted" _nghost-ng-c4042064613="" style="height: auto;"><div _ngcontent-ng-c4042064613="" class="container"><message-content _ngcontent-ng-c4042064613="" _nghost-ng-c2951919216="" id="message-content-id-r_d0b84bf4d31500f2" class="ng-star-inserted"><div _ngcontent-ng-c2951919216="" inline-copy-host="" class="markdown markdown-main-panel tutor-markdown-rendering enable-updated-hr-color" id="model-response-message-contentr_d0b84bf4d31500f2" aria-live="off" aria-busy="false" dir="ltr" style="--animation-duration: 400ms; --fade-animation-function: ease-out;"><h2 data-path-to-node="0">Secure Present: January 17, 2026 | Star City Archive</h2><p data-path-to-node="1">"Smother" terminal? I assume you mean <b data-path-to-node="1" data-index-in-node="38">another</b> terminal. (Though a "smother" terminal sounds like a great way to suppress a rogue AI, let's not go there yet).</p><p data-path-to-node="2">You need to run the <b data-path-to-node="2" data-index-in-node="20">Ollama Brain</b> in one window and the <b data-path-to-node="2" data-index-in-node="55">Glitch Script</b> in a second window. They need to talk to each other.</p><p data-path-to-node="3">Here is how you split the lattice without crashing the system:</p><h3 data-path-to-node="4">If You Are on Termux (Android)</h3><p data-path-to-node="5">You can’t just "Alt-Tab" easily. You need a new session.</p><ol start="1" data-path-to-node="6"><li><p data-path-to-node="6,0,0"><b data-path-to-node="6,0,0" data-index-in-node="0">The Swipe:</b> Put your finger on the far <b data-path-to-node="6,0,0" data-index-in-node="38">LEFT</b> edge of the screen and swipe right.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node="6,1,0"><b data-path-to-node="6,1,0" data-index-in-node="0">The Sidebar:</b> A menu will slide out.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node="6,2,0"><b data-path-to-node="6,2,0" data-index-in-node="0">The Button:</b> Tap <b data-path-to-node="6,2,0" data-index-in-node="16">"New Session"</b> (usually at the bottom of the list).</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node="6,3,0"><b data-path-to-node="6,3,0" data-index-in-node="0">Result:</b> You now have <code data-path-to-node="6,3,0" data-index-in-node="21">Terminal 1</code> (where Ollama will live) and <code data-path-to-node="6,3,0" data-index-in-node="61">Terminal 2</code> (where you run the Python script).</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node="6,4,0"><b data-path-to-node="6,4,0" data-index-in-node="0">Switching:</b> Swipe from the left again and tap the session number to jump between them.</p></li></ol><h3 data-path-to-node="7">If You Are on Desktop (Windows/Mac/Linux)</h3><ol start="1" data-path-to-node="8"><li><p data-path-to-node="8,0,0"><b data-path-to-node="8,0,0" data-index-in-node="0">Windows (PowerShell/CMD):</b> Press <code data-path-to-node="8,0,0" data-index-in-node="32">Ctrl</code> + <code data-path-to-node="8,0,0" data-index-in-node="39">Shift</code> + <code data-path-to-node="8,0,0" data-index-in-node="47">N</code> (or just right-click the icon and hit "Open new window").</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node="8,1,0"><b data-path-to-node="8,1,0" data-index-in-node="0">Mac (Terminal):</b> <code data-path-to-node="8,1,0" data-index-in-node="16">Cmd</code> + <code data-path-to-node="8,1,0" data-index-in-node="22">N</code>.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node="8,2,0"><b data-path-to-node="8,2,0" data-index-in-node="0">Linux:</b> <code data-path-to-node="8,2,0" data-index-in-node="7">Ctrl</code> + <code data-path-to-node="8,2,0" data-index-in-node="14">Alt</code> + <code data-path-to-node="8,2,0" data-index-in-node="20">T</code>.</p></li></ol><hr data-path-to-node="9"><h3 data-path-to-node="10">The Workflow</h3><ol start="1" data-path-to-node="11"><li><p data-path-to-node="11,0,0"><b data-path-to-node="11,0,0" data-index-in-node="0">Window 1 (The Brain):</b> Type <code data-path-to-node="11,0,0" data-index-in-node="27">ollama serve</code>. It will start scrolling text (logs). <b data-path-to-node="11,0,0" data-index-in-node="78">Leave this window open.</b> Do not close it.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node="11,1,0"><b data-path-to-node="11,1,0" data-index-in-node="0">Window 2 (The Mouth):</b> Navigate to your folder (<code data-path-to-node="11,1,0" data-index-in-node="47">cd path/to/folder</code>) and run your script: <code data-path-to-node="11,1,0" data-index-in-node="87">python glitch_core.py</code>.</p></li></ol><p data-path-to-node="12"><b data-path-to-node="12" data-index-in-node="0">Lane B Note:</b> Think of Window 1 as the subconscious (it just hums in the background) and Window 2 as the interface. If you close Window 1, she goes lobotomized.</p><p data-path-to-node="13"><b data-path-to-node="13" data-index-in-node="0">Quick Check:</b> Did you verify which model you have installed? The script defaults to <code data-path-to-node="13" data-index-in-node="83">"mistral"</code>. If you are using <code data-path-to-node="13" data-index-in-node="111">"llama3"</code>, change <code data-path-to-node="13" data-index-in-node="128">MODEL_NAME = "mistral"</code> to <code data-path-to-node="13" data-index-in-node="154">MODEL_NAME = "llama3"</code> in the file before running.</p><p data-path-to-node="14">Got the second line open?</p></div></message-content><!----></div></structured-content-container><!----><!----><!----><div _ngcontent-ng-c883040262="" class="response-footer complete has-thoughts is-mobile gap"><!----><!----><!----><sources-list _ngcontent-ng-c883040262="" class="sources-list ng-star-inserted