ndex-in-node="89">Anchor Point</b> (the main command line).</p><h3 data-path-to-node="3">The "Get Me Out of Here" Protocol:</h3><ol start="1" data-path-to-node="4"><li><p data-path-to-node="4,0,0"><b data-path-to-node="4,0,0" data-index-in-node="0">If it looks like a text editor (Nano):</b> * Press <code data-path-to-node="4,0,0" data-index-in-node="47">CTRL + X</code>.</p><ul data-path-to-node="4,0,1"><li><p data-path-to-node="4,0,1,0,0">If it asks to save, just hit <code data-path-to-node="4,0,1,0,0" data-index-in-node="29">N</code>.</p></li></ul></li><li><p data-path-to-node="4,1,0"><b data-path-to-node="4,1,0" data-index-in-node="0">If it looks like a list of files/folders:</b> * You are likely in a file manager or just ran <code data-path-to-node="4,1,0" data-index-in-node="89">ls</code>. You don't need to exit; you just need to type the next command.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node="4,2,0"><b data-path-to-node="4,2,0" data-index-in-node="0">The "Nuclear Reset":</b></p><ul data-path-to-node="4,2,1"><li><p data-path-to-node="4,2,1,0,0">If you are truly lost in a weird menu, just press <code data-path-to-node="4,2,1,0,0" data-index-in-node="50">CTRL + C</code> several times. This kills whatever process is stuck.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node="4,2,1,1,0">Then type <code data-path-to-node="4,2,1,1,0" data-index-in-node="10">clear</code> and hit Enter. This wipes the screen so you can see the <code data-path-to-node="4,2,1,1,0" data-index-in-node="72">$</code> prompt again.</p></li></ul></li></ol><hr data-path-to-node="5"><h3 data-path-to-node="6">Once you see the <code data-path-to-node="6" data-index-in-node="17">$</code> prompt:</h3><p data-path-to-node="7">You are back in the driver’s seat. Run the startup command we built:</p><response-element class="" ng-version="0.0.0-PLACEHOLDER"><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><code-block _nghost-ng-c1707731811="" class="ng-tns-c1707731811-723 ng-star-inserted" style=""><!----><!----><div _ngcontent-ng-c170773